        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Prompt and Context Lineage Tracking"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Every Claude response is a function of everything that went into its context window: the user's message, retrieved documents, system instructions, prior conversation turns, and tool outputs. Without lineage tracking, you cannot answer a regulator's question about where a particular output came from, reproduce a prior result for debugging, or demonstrate to a compliance auditor which data sources influenced a high-stakes AI decision."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Prompt and context lineage graph diagram",
          "title": null
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The lineage graph above shows how each input span (user prompt, RAG retrieval, system prompt, tool output) is captured with a unique span ID, assembled into a traced context, sent to Claude, and recorded in an immutable lineage store alongside the response."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What Prompt Lineage Means"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Prompt lineage is the complete, reproducible record of every piece of information that entered a Claude API call. It answers:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Provenance:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " which documents, database records, or tool responses contributed to this context?"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Reproducibility:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " if the same context were assembled today, would Claude produce the same output?"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Attribution:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " when a response contains a specific claim, which source document is the origin?"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Deletion propagation:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " if a source document is deleted under GDPR Art. 17, which AI responses must be flagged or retracted?"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Lineage is not the same as logging. A log captures that something happened. Lineage captures the causal graph: what inputs produced what outputs, and through which transformations."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Lineage Data Model"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Model each Claude interaction as a trace containing multiple spans. This maps directly to the OpenTelemetry standard, making integration with existing observability infrastructure straightforward."
          }
        ]
