      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Prompt and context lineage tracking gives enterprises the causal graph they need to answer governance questions: what inputs produced a given Claude output, which source documents were involved, and what would need to be flagged if a source were retracted. Implement it by modelling each interaction as a trace with typed spans (user input, RAG retrieval, system prompt, tool call, context assembly, API call, response), recording a stable hash of each input rather than the raw text, and writing spans to an append-only store. Query the store to propagate deletions, reproduce historical results, and package evidence for regulators and auditors. OpenTelemetry integration allows lineage spans to appear in standard observability tooling alongside service-level traces."
